    <section class="view is-active" id="view-overview" data-view="overview">
      <header class="view-head"><h1><svg class="icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#icon-overview"/></svg>Overview</h1></header>

      <details class="guide">
        <summary>How to read this report</summary>
        <div class="body">
          <p>This report shows where your Claude Code spend went in the selected window, and where it's likely worth attention. Each section in the left nav is one perspective on the same data:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Cost</strong> — dollars sliced by model, project, skill / slash command, and prompt</li>
            <li><strong>Sessions</strong> — a drill-down into individual sessions, the prompts inside them, and the assistant turns each prompt produced</li>
            <li><strong>Cache efficiency</strong> — how much of your context paid full price vs the cheap cache-read price</li>
            <li><strong>Tools</strong> — which tools (Read, Bash, Edit…) drove the most spend</li>
            <li><strong>Subagents</strong> — main thread vs sidechain, and which subagent types cost most</li>
          </ul>
          <p><strong>How to use it:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>The <strong>hotspots</strong> below are the highest-leverage targets in this window. Open a card, click <strong>Copy prompt</strong>, paste into Claude (or any LLM) for tailored remediation advice. Prompt-kind hotspots also carry a <em>view session →</em> button that jumps to the session drill-down with the originating prompt pre-expanded.</li>
            <li>The <strong>trend chart</strong> at the bottom of this view flags anomalies inline: an enlarged coral dot with a small <code>▲ 3.4×</code> or <code>▼ −32pp</code> marker is a bucket whose cost spiked or whose cache hit ratio dropped well outside the trailing-7-bucket baseline. Hover the dot for the exact multiplier or pp-gap.</li>
            <li><strong>Hover any column header</strong> for a one-line definition of that metric.</li>
            <li>Each section opens with a callout like this one — short rules of thumb for what high values usually mean and what to try.</li>
            <li>The <strong>Filter</strong> and <strong>Min cost</strong> controls at the top apply across every section.</li>
            <li><strong>Deep-link anchors</strong> on hotspot and session cards (the small <code>#</code> next to the cost) copy a shareable URL that opens the card and scrolls it into view.</li>
            <li>Save as PDF (Cmd-P / Ctrl-P) to get a print-friendly single-document copy — every <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> body is force-expanded and the sidebar drops out.</li>
          </ul>
          {{if .ServeMode}}
          <p><strong>Running under <code>claudit serve</code>:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>The <strong>calendar button</strong> in the sidebar (next to the claudit logo) opens a date-range picker. Apply navigates to a URL with <code>since</code>/<code>until</code> set; Clear strips the date filter and lifts server defaults. End is inclusive in the picker.</li>
            <li>The scope note in the filter bar (e.g. <em>"Showing last 7 days · top 10 sessions · show all"</em>) appears whenever server defaults are narrowing the view. Click <strong>show all</strong> to load the full archive for this one request.</li>
            <li><strong>The URL is the filter.</strong> Any query param the report CLI accepts works in the address bar: <code>?project=myrepo&amp;last=7d</code>, <code>?since=2026-05-01&amp;until=2026-05-15&amp;by=week</code>, <code>?hotspots=5&amp;sessions=20&amp;redact=true</code>. Bookmark a URL to bookmark a filter.</li>
            <li><strong>Auto-reload</strong> is silent and runs every 30 s. It defers while you're reading (any <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> open, recent mouse/keyboard activity, or tab hidden) and resumes the moment the page is idle. If new data has been pending more than 5 minutes, a toast in the bottom-right offers a manual reload.</li>
          </ul>
          {{end}}
        </div>
      </details>

